solutions.content:
Go column by column ```c```, then row by row ```i```. If ```A[i - 1][c] > A[i][c]```, then that column is unsorted - we increase the number of deleted columns and go to the next column.
```
int minDeletionSize(vector<string>& A, int res = 0) {
    if (A.empty()) return res;
    for (auto c = 0; c < A[0].size(); ++c)
        for (auto i = 1; i < A.size(); ++i) {
            if (A[i - 1][c] > A[i][c]) {
                ++res;
                break;
            }
        }
    return res;
}
```

