# Intuition
**Basically 2-D vector traversal**
# Approach
First, we are traversing throgh the entire string vector and checking whether the first character  of consecutive strings are in alphabetical order or not ,then the second character ...... upto the last character.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
# **O(n*m)**
where n = size of each individual string 
      m = size of string vector

- Space complexity:
# **O(1)**

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDeletionSize(vector<string>& strs) {
        int ans =0 , n=strs[1].size();
        int  j=0;
        while(j<n){
            int i=0;
            while(i<(strs.size())-1){
                string a = strs[i] ,b = strs[i+1];
                if(a[j] <= b[j]){
                    i++;
                }
                else{
                    ans++;
                    i++;
                    break;
                }
            }
