solutions.content:
**Approach** : For every column, we keep track of the largest character visited, if we encounter a smaller character, that column has to be deleted

Consider the following `strs`
```
["qowfc","spyge","sqbif","vvrkk"]⤵

    |q o w f c|
	|s p y g e|     
	|s q b i f|
	|v v r k k|
```
For the `1st` column we have `q <= s <= s <= v`, this column will not be deleted ( similary `2nd ,4th` column)
For the `3rd` column we have `w <= y > b <= r`


**Time Complexity** : O(N*M)
**Space Complexity** : O(1)

Implementation
```
class Solution {
    public int minDeletionSize(String[] strs) {

        int n = strs.length, m = strs[0].length(),ans = 0;

        for(int j = 0;j<m;j++){

            int prev = 0; // largest previous character so far (we initialize this with 'a')

            boolean toBeDeleted = false; 

            for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){

                int cur = strs[i].charAt(j) - 'a';

                if(cur >= prev){   // update prev if we get a larger character

                    prev = cur;

                }else{  // otherwise this column will be deleted

                    toBeDeleted = true;

                    break;

                }


            }

            if(toBeDeleted) ans++; // increment count of deleted columns

        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

